"{\"uid\": \"standard.co.uk-news-uk-liverpool-katarina-johnsonthompson-belgian-paris-olympics-b1175829.html\", \"text\": \"To use the search feature, we need your consent to load Google Custom Search, which may use cookies or similar technologies. Please click 'Allow and Continue' below to enable search. See our privacy policy for more information.  News|UK  Katarina Johnson-Thompsonhas described her love forLiverpooland how the city gave her a \\\"never-give-up attitude\\\", after winning her first Olympic medal.  The Liverpudlian took silver in the heptathlon on Friday inParis, coming second toBelgianrival Nafissatou Thiam.  Johnson-Thompson, 31, on Saturday spoke about her love for Liverpool and how it shaped her as a person.  I love the people of Liverpool and I love what they stand for and that shapes my character, of that never-give-up attitude, and that underdog attitude and yes, it means the world  Katarina Johnson-Thompson  She said: \\\"Liverpool is my home, it always is my home even if I train and live elsewhere.  \\\"I love the people of Liverpool and I love what they stand for and that shapes my character, of that never-give-up attitude, and that underdog attitude and yes, it means the world.  \\\"I started my career at Liverpool Harriers and I am indebted to them as well.\\\"  Johnson-Thompson said the silver medal was \\\"a long time coming\\\".  \\\"It feels incredible that you know we got one over the line. It's been a long time coming, it's been a very short cycle but it's my fourthOlympicsand I am really happy to add that medal to my collection,\\\" she said.  Johnson-Thompson said: \\\"I have got absolutely no regrets. I tried my absolute best and my best on that day was second place by about 30 points, so you know I was very close to an Olympic gold medal and to me that's just validated our team's belief that it was possible.\\\"  Asked if there were times she doubted she would get there, she said: \\\"I have had doubts all the time, every athlete I feel like, even if they do not admit it, always has doubts - crippling doubts, but luckily I have got a team around me that has the belief in me that I sometimes do not have in myself, and that leads me to do great things and I am so grateful to them.\\\"  Asked about her plans for the future, she said: \\\"I feel like as long as I am competitive I will continue to do heptathlon.  \\\"I am really happy that I am able to put together my heptathlon in a different way now and it's given me such longevity in the sport.  \\\"I am really really excited for the next couple of years.\\\"  MORE ABOUT  1  Crime  Fight breaks out on Elizabeth line train after youths told to stop vaping by middle-aged passenger  Fight breaks out on Elizabeth line after youths told to stop vaping  2  Football  Liverpool XI vs Brighton: Starting lineup, confirmed team news, injury latest for Premier League today  Liverpool XI vs Brighton: Starting lineup and confirmed team news  3  UK  Flights alert: UK issues global travel disruption warning over Donald Trump's Iran war  Flights alert: UK issues global travel disruption warning on Iran war  4  Lifestyle  Horoscope today: Your daily guide for Saturday, March 21, 2026  Horoscope today: Your daily guide for Saturday, March 21, 2026  5  Football  Arsenal XI vs Man City: Confirmed team news, predicted lineup, injury latest for Carabao Cup final  Arsenal XI vs Man City: Confirmed team news and predicted lineup\"}"